List of elements of S4subscript𝑆4S_{4} ordered in 3 families.
kisubscript𝑘𝑖k_{i} denote the elements of K and (a↔b)↔𝑎𝑏(a\leftrightarrow b) a
simple permutation where a and b are interchanged.
Permutations with a 4 at the last position form
a S3subscript𝑆3S_{3} subgroup of S4subscript𝑆4S_{4} and may be thought of giving the set
of lepton states.
It should be noted that this is only a heuristic
assignment. Actually one has to consider linear combinations
of permutation states as discussed in section 2.
